- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possibility as the paper uses a weighted version of the second moment method, which involves numerical computations. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as independent sets are relevant in the study of social and information networks. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper may have implications for the computational complexity of finding maximum independent sets in random graphs.
